<div class="page-header">
<h2>Anthrocon </h2>
<p><img src="http://www.anthrocon.org/files/anthrocon/group.jpg" alt="Anthrocon" width="400" height="auto" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;" /></p>
<p> Anthrocon is the world's largest convention dedicated exclusively to cartoon animal fandom. Last year, 5,861 cartoon animals filled the city of Pittsburgh. This year the event will be held at David L. Lawrence Convention Center on the weekend of July 9-12, 2015. Interesting characters will be all over the city. The Hyatt hotel does not house members from the conference, but the Marriott city center does. Enjoy the eye candy!
</p></div>

<div class="page-header">
<h2>The Heinz History Center</h2>
<p><img src="http://cravecoasters.files.wordpress.com/2012/01/img_6314.jpg" alt="Heinz History Center" width="400" height="auto" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;" /></p>
<p> As a guest of our wedding you have free access to the history center during the afternoon of July 11! After our ceremony at St. Mary's of the Mount, gather your things and head to the Heinz History Center. The exhibits range from a fully dedicated sports museum, Senator John Heinz: A Western Pennsylvania Legacy to miniature rollarcoast rides, mimicking our beloved Kennywood. </p> 
